1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:06,620
We can add other conditional logic to our loops for other intermediary statements.

2

00:00:06,620  -->  00:00:10,780
Let's take a look at how to upgrade our four loops to include an else clause,

3

00:00:10,780  -->  00:00:14,205
which will execute a condition once the loop completes.

4

00:00:14,205  -->  00:00:16,400
Let's take our range function and add

5

00:00:16,400  -->  00:00:20,660
an else statement to it so that once a range of five is reached,

6

00:00:20,660  -->  00:00:25,120
we'll print the loop as it's finished.

7

00:00:25,600  -->  00:00:34,220
We'll do that by writing a four loop with four I in range five.

8

00:00:34,220  -->  00:00:38,440
We'll do colon, and we'll say print I.

9

00:00:40,580  -->  00:00:47,940
Else. We'll say print, loop, just finished.

10

00:00:49,820  -->  00:00:52,540
Do you see what's happening now?

11

00:00:52,540  -->  00:00:54,660
Once the number four,

12

00:00:54,660  -->  00:00:58,100
which is position five is reached,

13

00:00:58,100  -->  00:01:03,095
the condition will be met and the value will no longer be true but false.

14

00:01:03,095  -->  00:01:07,300
Thus the else clause will be invoked.

15

00:01:07,300  -->  00:01:14,220
Can you guess what's going to happen when we execute this cell? Let's find out.

16

00:01:15,680  -->  00:01:19,550
We'll see the numbers zero, one, two, three,

17

00:01:19,550  -->  00:01:21,250
four, printed out,

18

00:01:21,250  -->  00:01:23,230
and then the final statement,

19

00:01:23,230  -->  00:01:26,830
Luke finished is printed at the end,

20

00:01:26,830  -->  00:01:30,790
because we've iterated through all of the numbers in range five,

21

00:01:30,790  -->  00:01:34,335
and then we invoke our else statement.

22

00:01:34,335  -->  00:01:36,630
If you said this, great job.

23

00:01:36,630  -->  00:01:40,100
When would we use else in loops?

24

00:01:40,100  -->  00:01:43,660
The first is confirmation when the loop completed.

25

00:01:43,660  -->  00:01:47,900
The else clause is useful when you need to confirm that

26

00:01:47,900  -->  00:01:53,180
the loop has run through all iterations before being interrupted by a break statement.

27

00:01:53,180  -->  00:01:58,640
This can be particularly helpful in search algorithms or when processing collections.

28

00:01:58,640  -->  00:02:02,460
Second up is searching for an item in a list.

29

00:02:02,460  -->  00:02:05,060
Imagine you're searching for an item in a list.

30

00:02:05,060  -->  00:02:07,740
If the item is found, you break the loop.

31

00:02:07,740  -->  00:02:11,040
If the item is not found after all iterations,

32

00:02:11,040  -->  00:02:15,105
you can use the else clause to handle this scenario.

33

00:02:15,105  -->  00:02:16,830
In this example here,

34

00:02:16,830  -->  00:02:18,830
if the search item is found,

35

00:02:18,830  -->  00:02:22,110
the loop breaks, and the else clause is not executed.

36

00:02:22,110  -->  00:02:24,270
If the search item is not found,

37

00:02:24,270  -->  00:02:26,570
the else clause is executed,

38

00:02:26,570  -->  00:02:29,780
indicating the item was not found in the list.

39

00:02:29,780  -->  00:02:33,600
As we see here, grape fruit is not found in this list.

40

00:02:33,600  -->  00:02:36,550
The else clause is executed here.

41

00:02:36,550  -->  00:02:39,700
Third, we can validate input data with else.

42

00:02:39,700  -->  00:02:44,280
When validating input data or confirming if something is true or not,

43

00:02:44,280  -->  00:02:48,580
you might loop through a set of conditions logic and use

44

00:02:48,580  -->  00:02:53,580
the else clause to confirm that all conditions are met without any issues.

45

00:02:53,580  -->  00:02:55,680
In this case here,

46

00:02:55,680  -->  00:02:58,040
if a negative number is found,

47

00:02:58,040  -->  00:03:01,420
the loop breaks, and the else clause is not executed.

48

00:03:01,420  -->  00:03:03,260
If all numbers are positive,

49

00:03:03,260  -->  00:03:05,040
the else clause confirms this,

50

00:03:05,040  -->  00:03:08,240
as we see here with the else clause being

51

00:03:08,240  -->  00:03:12,100
executed as all numbers are positive and greater than zero.

52

00:03:12,100  -->  00:03:15,460
Last up, we can combine else with while loops.

53

00:03:15,460  -->  00:03:18,700
The else clause is not limited to four loops.

54

00:03:18,700  -->  00:03:21,235
It can also be used with while loops.

55

00:03:21,235  -->  00:03:24,380
This can be useful for scenarios where you want to

56

00:03:24,380  -->  00:03:28,000
ensure that a condition was met throughout the entire loop,

57

00:03:28,000  -->  00:03:30,940
such as counting up to the limit and then

58

00:03:30,940  -->  00:03:34,680
printing a message at the end as while completes.

59

00:03:34,680  -->  00:03:39,040
While we add this powerful clause else to our Pythonic toolkit,

60

00:03:39,040  -->  00:03:42,740
there are some things to note about how it works that are worth

61

00:03:42,740  -->  00:03:47,220
going over so that you don't make these mistakes when you write your loops in logic.

62

00:03:47,220  -->  00:03:51,020
Number one, else is not an alternative to I.

63

00:03:51,020  -->  00:03:54,080
It's important to note that the else clause in

64

00:03:54,080  -->  00:03:57,220
loops is not an alternative to using if statements.

65

00:03:57,220  -->  00:04:01,840
It serves as a different purpose by providing a way to execute code after

66

00:04:01,840  -->  00:04:07,560
the loop finishes provided it wasn't terminated prematurely by a break. Number two.

67

00:04:07,560  -->  00:04:11,830
Else clause executes after normal loop termination.

68

00:04:11,830  -->  00:04:17,890
The else clause only executes if the loop completes all iterations normally.

69

00:04:17,890  -->  00:04:20,430
If the loop is terminated by a break statement,

70

00:04:20,430  -->  00:04:23,050
the else clause will not be executed.

71

00:04:23,050  -->  00:04:25,730
With these two helpful strategies in mind,

72

00:04:25,730  -->  00:04:30,310
you'll be ready to tackle adding else to your loops.
